OL,3,GStrathclyde
OL,4,
OL,5,CThis Evening and Tonight:FCloud
OL,6,Fbecoming thicker this evening to bring
OL,7,Foccasional rain, which will be mostly
OL,8,Flight and mainly confined to Argyll.
OL,9,FDrier spells developing over Argyll by
OL,10,Fdawn. Southerly coastal winds
OL,11,Finitially fresh.
OL,12,
OL,13,CWednesday:FTemperatures will feel
OL,14,Fsignificantly cooler than Tuesday.
OL,15,FRather cloudy morning with a little
OL,16,Flight and patchy rain, mostly confined
OL,17,Facross Argyll. Dry for the afternoon
OL,18,Fwith brighter spells.
OL,23,QppppppppppppppppppppGSource: Met Office
